Instead, you should use the iterator you've created in the outer loop and call next() on it in each iteration of the inner loop.
Here's how you can do it:
Iterator<DataSnapshot> it = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator();
while(it.hasNext()) {
    DataSnapshot ds = it.next();
    names.add(ds.getValue(String.class));
}

This way, you're using the same iterator throughout the loop, and you're getting the next child in each iteration.

